		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just wanna state that I'm all the way with Disch on this one.
<br />
<br />You know, even when cutscenes are DA SHIT, perfect in every possible way, I will still most likely only want to watch them the first couple of times I play through the game. They should always be skippable.
<br />
<br />I also believe that games should be self-contained products. I shouldn't need a manual or any info besides what's on the cartridge/CD/other media in order to play it... You see, these things may get lost with time, pausing the game to look stuff up somewhere else is not convenient at all, and so on. I would most likely get frustrated with a game like that and move on without thinking twice.

		

